Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Knidian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay near fine light orange-brown; some mica. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol.
Type series: KT675 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 201, 24. Names, Aristokles, Eniochos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0303)
